-- PRESS DIGEST- New York Times business news - March 10
-- 
-- Mon Mar 10, 2014 01:24AM EDT
-- None



March 10 (Reuters) - The following are the top stories on the New York Times business pages. Reuters has not verified these stories and does not vouch for their accuracy.

* BlackRock, the world's largest asset-management company, said on Monday that it had hired Helen Zhu as a managing director and head of its China equities business. (http://r.reuters.com/jub57v)  * A federal jury on Friday found Jesse C. Litvak, a former senior trader at the Jefferies Group, guilty of deceiving his customers about the prices of mortgage-backed securities he sold to them after the financial crisis. (http://r.reuters.com/xeb57v)  * New York Public Radio will announce on Monday that it has received a $10 million grant from the Jerome L. Greene Foundation, which it says is the largest single gift ever made to a public radio station. (http://r.reuters.com/zeb57v)  * Microsoft Corp <MSFT.O> is betting that a new game, Titanfall, will be enough of a hit to improve sales of its flagship gaming console Xbox One, whose sales are trailing those of a machine from Sony, Microsoft's main rival. (http://r.reuters.com/bub57v)  * The British financier Guy Hands has agreed to end a lawsuit against Citigroup Inc <C.N> in the United States, though the legal battle may continue in England. (http://r.reuters.com/cub57v)  * Tencent Holdings Ltd <0700.HK>, one of China's biggest Internet companies, said on Monday it would pay $215 million for a 15 percent stake in the Chinese e-commerce company JD.com. (http://r.reuters.com/dub57v)